fields.description:
We have added option to pull request creation page, via FormFragment. When it executed, we store some information into database.

We also have:
{code}
    @EventListener
    public void opened(PullRequestOpenedEvent e) {
       ...
    }
{code}

In this listener we try to read value stored from ForFragment on PR creation. And sometimes we did not found anything in database when listener invoked.

Under this documentation (https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/STASH/Using+the+Stash+Backup+Client), the backup client requried parameters *are missing* after this paragraph:
{quote}
Configuration options are kept in the backup-config.properties file that is included with the client – this file is automatically read when the client is run. The required properties include:
{quote}

Given I've created a repo {{guides.git}} that contains e.g.

{noformat}
-
 |- CONTRIBUTING.md
 |- GETTING_STARTED.md
 |- README.md
{noformat}

When my {{README.md}} contains.

{code}
# Index of guides

* [Getting Started](GETTING_STARTED.md)
* [Contribution Process](CONTRIBUTING.md)
{code}

Then if I view the repository {{/guides/browse}} (i.e. do not view the README.md file directly,  but get the implicit rendering when viewing a repository's page) then the links do not resolve correctly, they resolve to {{/guides/GETTING_STARTED.md}}.

If I view the README.md file directly {{/guides/browse/README.md}}, then I correctly get them resolved {{/guides/browse/GETTING_STARTED.md}}

The following for example doesn't work:
{code}
Text (**bold**) text.
{code}

Meanwhile, if there is a space between the parentheses and markdown, it works as expected:
{code}
Text ( **bold**) text.
{code}

This issue was reported to [GitHub|https://github.com/github/markup/issues/167] as well and it was fixed
